  "content": "kens,\n            };\n            (Some(result.text), Some(metrics))\n        } else {\n            (None, None)\n        };\n\n        let total_ms = pipeline_start.elapsed().as_millis() as u64;\n        info!(total_latency_ms = total_ms, \"rag_query_completed\");\n\n        let trace = PipelineTrace {\n            trace_id,\n            retrieval: retrieval.metrics,\n            augmentation: AugmentationMetrics {\n                latency_ms: augment_ms,\n                ..augmented.metrics.clone()\n            },\n            generation: gen_metrics,\n            total_latency_ms: total_ms,\n        };\n\n        Ok(RagResponse {\n            answer,\n            context: augmented,\n            trace,\n        })\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Step 4: Add module to lib.rs**\n\nIn `crates/corvia-kernel/src/lib.rs`, add after `pub mod augmenter;`:\n\n```rust\npub mod rag_pipeline;\n```\n\n**Step 5: Run tests to verify they pass**\n\nRun: `cargo test -p corvia-kernel -- rag_pipeline::tests --nocapture`\nExpected: all 4 tests PASS\n\n**Step 6: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add crates/corvia-kernel/src/rag_pipeline.rs crates/corvia-kernel/src/lib.rs\ngit commit -m \"feat(m3.2): RagPipeline — orchestrator with context() and ask() modes\"\n```\n\n---\n",
